'''2016年美国民主党全国委员会邮件泄密事件'''，又被称为“'''[[希拉里·克林顿电子邮件争议|邮件门]]2.0'''”<ref name="kknews">{{cite web|url=http://www.kankanews.com/a/2016-07-26/0037620618.shtml|title=希拉里"邮件门2.0"：美国大选到底有多肮脏？|publisher=看看新闻网|author=左禾欢|accessdate=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808052934/http://www.kankanews.com/a/2016-07-26/0037620618.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是2016年[[美国民主党|美国民主党]][[民主党全国委员会|全国委员会]]的内部邮件被[[维基解密|维基解密]]网站公开的事件，被披露的包括19252封电子邮件和8034份附件<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/07/22/on-eve-of-democratic-convention-wikileaks-releases-thousands-of-documents-about-clinton-the-campaign-and-internal-deliberations/ |title=WikiLeaks releases thousands of documents about Clinton and internal deliberations |author=Karen Tumulty |author2=Tom Hamburger |last-author-amp=yes |newspaper=Washington Post |date=2016-08-24 |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822095057/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/07/22/on-eve-of-democratic-convention-wikileaks-releases-thousands-of-documents-about-clinton-the-campaign-and-internal-deliberations/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这些邮件涉及了七位民主党内重量级人物，时间跨度从2015年1月到2016年5月<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-switch/wp/2016/07/22/wikileaks-posts-nearly-20000-hacked-dnc-emails-online/ |title=Wikileaks posts nearly 20,000 hacked DNC emails online |author=Andrea Peterson |newspaper=Washington Post |date=2016-08-24 |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031075442/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-switch/wp/2016/07/22/wikileaks-posts-nearly-20000-hacked-dnc-emails-online/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，内容涉及对[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]的党内竞争对手[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]及[[共和黨_(美國)|共和党]]总统参选人[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]的抹黑，以及民主党内的财务问题。这次事件直接导致包括主席{{le|黛比·舒尔茨|Debbie Wasserman Schultz}}在内的多位民主党全国委员会高层辞职<ref>{{cite news |first1=Jonathan |last1=Martin |first2=Alan |last2=Rappeport |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/25/us/politics/debbie-wasserman-schultz-dnc-wikileaks-emails.html?_r=1 |title=Debbie Wasserman Schultz to Resign D.N.C. Post |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2016-08-24 |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728060537/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/25/us/politics/debbie-wasserman-schultz-dnc-wikileaks-emails.html?_r=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/08/02/politics/dnc-ceo-resigns-in-wake-of-email-scandal/index.html | title=DNC CEO resigns in wake of email controversy | publisher=CNN | accessdate=2016-08-24 | archive-date=2016-08-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818183130/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/08/02/politics/dnc-ceo-resigns-in-wake-of-email-scandal/index.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。最终民主党全国委员会向桑德斯及其支持者致歉，承认这些邮件并没有反映出选举期间应有的中立立场<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-dnc-statement-idUSKCN1052BN |title=Democratic National Committee apologizes to Sanders over emails |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817192312/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-dnc-statement-idUSKCN1052BN |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==邮件内容==
被公开的邮件内容揭示了民主党全国委员会与媒体之间的互动，希拉里和桑德斯的竞选活动以及政治献金情况。除此之外，部分捐赠者的个人信息也被泄露，包括他们的[[信用卡|信用卡]]信息及[[社会保障号码|社会保障号码]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=McCarthy|first1=Kieren|title=WikiLeaks fights The Man by, er, publishing ordinary people's personal information|url=http://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/07/22/wikileaks_keep_fighting_the_man_by_er_publishing_the_personal_details_of_ordinary_citizens/|website=The Register|accessdate=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822191359/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/07/22/wikileaks_keep_fighting_the_man_by_er_publishing_the_personal_details_of_ordinary_citizens/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PetersonClash">{{cite web|author=Andrea Peterson|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-switch/wp/2016/07/28/a-twitter-spat-breaks-out-between-snowden-and-wikileaks/|title=Snowden and WikiLeaks clash over leaked Democratic Party emails|publisher=Washington Post|accessdate=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822082253/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-switch/wp/2016/07/28/a-twitter-spat-breaks-out-between-snowden-and-wikileaks/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===与媒体的关系===
邮件披露了民主党全国委员会雇员与多家媒体及其工作人员的“非正式”关系，包括[[有线电视新闻网|有线电视新闻网]]（CNN）、《[[华尔街日报|华尔街日报]]》、《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》和《[[政客_(杂志)|政客]]》杂志<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/presidential-races/289126-todd-tapper-respond-to-being-named-in-leaked-wikileaks|title=Todd, Tapper respond to being named in leaked WikiLeaks DNC emails|last=Joe|first=Concha|date=July 25, 2016|website=The Hill|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823050827/http://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/presidential-races/289126-todd-tapper-respond-to-being-named-in-leaked-wikileaks|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2016/07/24/wikileaks-emails-pro-clinton-cnn-political-commentator-pre-checked-op-ed-with-dnc/|title=WikiLeaks emails: Pro-Clinton CNN political commentator pre-checked op-ed with DNC|last=Wemple|first=Erik|date=July 24, 2016|newspaper=The Washington Post|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822095540/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2016/07/24/wikileaks-emails-pro-clinton-cnn-political-commentator-pre-checked-op-ed-with-dnc/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/25/us/politics/media-democratic-national-committee-emails.html|title=Ego Clashes Exposed in Leaked Emails From Democratic National Committee|last=Grynbaum|first=Michael M.|date=July 24, 2016|work=|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-08-24|via=|archive-date=2016-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825214414/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/25/us/politics/media-democratic-national-committee-emails.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CBS_SFBay_off">{{cite news |url=http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/2016/07/22/hilary-leaks-wikileaks-releases-democratic-national-committee-emails/ |title=WikiLeaks' DNC Email Leak Reveals Off The Record Media Correspondence |accessdate=2016-08-24 |publisher=SanFrancisco.cbslocal.com |archive-date=2016-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823060722/http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/2016/07/22/hilary-leaks-wikileaks-releases-democratic-national-committee-emails/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===打压桑德斯===
在被披露的邮件中，民主党全国委员会的职员多次表示出对桑德斯的嘲讽<ref name="ShearDerided">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/23/us/politics/dnc-emails-sanders-clinton.html|title=Released Emails Suggest the D.N.C. Derided the Sanders Campaign|last=Shear|first=Michael|accessdate=2016-08-24|newspaper=New York Times|archive-date=2016-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825214603/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/23/us/politics/dnc-emails-sanders-clinton.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《华盛顿邮报》报道称，许多人通过邮件对桑德斯进行攻击，他们还建议民主党全国委员会对桑德斯的竞选活动进行破坏<ref name=Here_are_the_latest>{{cite web |first=Aaron |last=Blake |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/07/24/here-are-the-latest-most-damaging-things-in-the-dncs-leaked-emails/ |title=Here are the latest, most damaging things in the DNC's leaked emails |newspaper=The Washington Post |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022085509/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/07/24/here-are-the-latest-most-damaging-things-in-the-dncs-leaked-emails/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2016年5月，民主党全国委员会[[首席财务官|首席财务官]]{{le|布拉德利·马歇尔|Bradley Marshall}}在写给民主党全国委员会[[首席执行官|首席执行官]]{{le|艾米·达西|Amy Dacey}}等人的邮件中对桑德斯的信仰进行了攻击<ref name="Here_are_the_latest" /><ref name="guardian">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jul/23/dnc-emails-wikileaks-hillary-bernie-sanders|title=Leaked DNC emails reveal details of anti-Sanders sentiment|last=|first=|date=July 24, 2016|work=|newspaper=The Guardian|agency=Associated Press|access-date=|via=|archive-date=2016-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724162752/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jul/23/dnc-emails-wikileaks-hillary-bernie-sanders|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而在全国委员会主席舒尔茨的邮件中更是毫不讳言：“他（桑德斯）当不了总统<ref name="ShearDerided"/>。”舒尔茨甚至称桑德斯的竞选经理是“该死的骗子”<ref name="Emails offer insights">{{cite web|url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/politics/sfl-emails-offer-insights-into-wasserman-schultz-at-dnc-20160724-story.html|title=Emails offer insights into Wasserman Schultz at DNC|last=Man|first=Anthony|date=July 23, 2016|website=[[Sun-Sentinel|Sun-Sentinel]]|publisher=Sun Sentinel|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826000116/http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/politics/sfl-emails-offer-insights-into-wasserman-schultz-at-dnc-20160724-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fox2now.com/2016/07/24/debbie-wasserman-schultz-no-longer-presiding-over-democratic-convention/|title=Debbie Wasserman Schultz no longer presiding over Democratic convention|last=|first=|date=2016-07-24|website=[[Fox_News_Channel|Fox News Channel]]|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827193835/http://fox2now.com/2016/07/24/debbie-wasserman-schultz-no-longer-presiding-over-democratic-convention/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/presidential-races/288904-wasserman-schultz-sanders-aide-a-damn-liar|title=Wasserman Schultz called top Sanders aide a 'damn liar' in leaked email|last=Carney|first=Jordain|date=2016-07-22|website=The Hill|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825105250/http://thehill.com/blogs/ballot-box/presidential-races/288904-wasserman-schultz-sanders-aide-a-damn-liar|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

另一封邮件指出，民主党公关主任将一封来自桑德斯竞选团队的[[PDF|PDF]]附件发送给了《华盛顿邮报》的记者，故意向媒体泄露桑德斯信息。除此之外，民主党全国委员会还勾结[[罗德岛州|罗德岛州]]政府打压桑德斯，因为桑德斯在此州支持率领先希拉里，民主党委员会就事先联系了罗德岛州长，让他变成“自己人”，不仅罗德岛政府统一口径，他们还只开放了部分投票点<ref name="kknews"/>。

===抹黑特朗普===
一份民主党高层邮件显示，他们计划冒充[[特朗普集团|特朗普集团]]发布一则招聘广告，内容充满了对女性的歧视，但最终这条广告并未发布<ref name="kknews"/>。另一封由一位名叫汤普森的民主党全国委员会职员发出的密送邮件显示，民主党负责网络传播的团队在[[Twitter|Twitter]]和[[Facebook|Facebook]]等社交媒体上持续推高有关特朗普危险言论的点击率，使其处于“讨论的前端”<ref name="nfw">{{Cite web|url=http://news.sohu.com/20160730/n461817702.shtml|title=美国大选“邮件门”：维基揭秘再曝29段音频|date=2016-07-30|website=搜狐|agency=南方网|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828171905/http://news.sohu.com/20160730/n461817702.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===涉嫌洗钱===
根据维基解密披露的邮件内容，“{{le|胜利基金|Victory Fund}}”（一家美国[[LGBT|LGBT]]权利机构）募集的6100万美元的资金中，只有不到1%的资金留在了民主党内的金库，其余部分全部流向了希拉里竞选团队，被指涉嫌洗钱<ref name="kknews"/>。

==反响及后续==

维基解密方面并未透露泄密者信息，但一名自称“{{le|古奇费尔2.0|Guccifer 2.0}}”的[[黑客|黑客]]宣称对泄密事件负责。有网络安全公司及美国情报官员宣称此事为[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]]情报部门所为，目的是为了帮助特朗普赢得大选。但此说法遭到维基解密、俄罗斯政府及“古奇费尔2.0”的一致否认<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://world.huanqiu.com/hot/2016-08/9274430.html|title=“邮件门”持续延烧 阿桑奇否认俄黑客窃取机密说法|date=2016-08-06|website=环球网|agency=法制日报|access-date=2016-08-24|archive-date=2018-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005144517/http://world.huanqiu.com/hot/2016-08/9274430.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="SpyAgencyConsensus">{{cite news|title=Spy Agency Consensus Grows That Russia Hacked D.N.C.|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/27/us/politics/spy-agency-consensus-grows-that-russia-hacked-dnc.html|work=|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=2016-08-24|archive-date=2016-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825214318/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/27/us/politics/spy-agency-consensus-grows-that-russia-hacked-dnc.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年7月25日，[[美国联邦调查局|美国联邦调查局]]（FBI）宣布介入调查<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-07-25/fbi-investigating-dnc-cyber-hack-some-democrats-blame-on-russia |title=FBI Investigating DNC Hack Some Democrats Blame on Russia |publisher=Bloomberg Politics |accessdate=2016-08-24 |archive-date=2016-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806213350/http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-07-25/fbi-investigating-dnc-cyber-hack-some-democrats-blame-on-russia |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crowdstrike.com/blog/bears-midst-intrusion-democratic-national-committee/|title=Bears in the Midst: Intrusion into the Democratic National Committee »|date=June 15, 2016|language=en-US|accessdate=2016-08-24|archive-date=2019-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524090240/https://www.crowdstrike.com/blog/bears-midst-intrusion-democratic-national-committee/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.threatgeek.com/2016/06/dnc_update.html|title=Findings from Analysis of DNC Intrusion Malware|website=T